  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "2) Sagunam: personal Creator God (11-17-80). Also Valis. Valis equals Brahman.\n\n\"Thus Sankara had a two-level theory of Brahman.\" I experienced the nirgunam or higher one in 3-74; sagunam, the lower one, in 11-17-80. But both are Brahman.\n\nThus 3-74 and 11-17-80 are reconciled by Sankara's two-level theory. I experienced Brahman both times, but the first was the impersonal qualityless and featureless Absolute, the second the lower way as the Creator of the world -- hence he possessed personal ch",
      "matched_alias": "Eastern",
      "term_id": "TERM_eastern",
      "term_name": "Eastern",
      "term_slug": "eastern"
    },
    {
      "text": "Complete\n23\n-15-80\n\nValis: set/ground. Camouflage. Here in the universe. Macrosoma blended into the universe in countless ways, here and there: a glint here, a word on a page, plural objects and their causal processes a ripple of wind in the weeds in the alley. Valis is not the universe but blended into it, as is Ubik. \"I am Atman that dwells in the heart of every mortal. I am Vishnu. I am Shiva. Among words I am the sacre syllable OM. I am Himalaya. I am the holy fig tree. Among horses I am...o",
      "matched_alias": "Krishna",
      "term_id": "TERM_krishna",
      "term_name": "Krishna",
      "term_slug": "krishna"
    }
  ],
